---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead  title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h2>🧑‍🚀 Welcome to Akrity.Work</h2>
			<p>
Akrity.Work is your go-to platform for keeping the team in sync and moving forward together. Whether it’s recapping a hectic sprint, tracking who’s tackling what, or sharing a sneak peek at the latest designs, this space has it all.
			</p>
			<p>
 Built with Astro for speed and simplicity, it’s designed to make collaboration a breeze—think of it as our team’s digital campfire where we gather to log updates, flag blockers, and celebrate progress. With custom components baked into easy-to-use MDX, anyone can jump in and contribute without missing a beat.
			</p>
			<p>Here are a few ideas on how to get started with the template:</p>
<ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li>Browse posts in <a href="/blog" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">src/content/blog/</a>.</li>
        <li>Add your own updates using our <a href="/about" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">cheat sheet</a>.</li>
        <li>Tweak the look in <code>src/layouts/</code> or <code>src/components/</code>.</li>
      </ul>
			<p>
What’s Happening

Check out our latest blog posts to see what the team’s been up to—meetings, blockers, code snippets, and more. It’s all written in simple MDX with custom components for a seamless flow.
			</p>
			<p>

Ready to dive in? Visit the blog or reach out on our team if you need help!
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
